  "prompt": "How do you calculate credit hours earned?",
  "response": "To calculate credit hours earned, follow these general steps:\n\n1. Check course credits\n- Each course is typically assigned a specific number of credit hours\n- Most standard college courses are 3 credit hours\n- Labs, workshops, and specialized courses may have different credit values\n\n2. Track completed courses\n- Record each course you successfully pass\n- Note the credit hours for each course\n- Multiply the course's credit hours by the grade received\n\n3. Grading scale calculation method\n- A = 4.0 points\n- B = 3.0 points\n- C = 2.0 points\n- D = 1.0 points\n- F = 0 points\n\n4. Calculate GPA and total credits\n- Multiply each course's credit hours by its grade points\n- Add up total grade points\n- Divide total grade points by total credit hours attempted\n\n5. Verify requirements\n- Check your specific school's credit hour policies\n- Confirm total credits needed for graduation\n- Ensure you've met all program requirements\n\n6. Use academic resources\n- Consult academic advisors\n- Review transcripts\n- Use online school portals for tracking\n\nAlways confirm specific details with your educational institution, as calculation methods can vary.",
